50 yen per minute
 An example of a ratio that is easy to understand in considering the exchange ratio of time and money.
 Of course, it varies several times from person to person, but the purpose is not to calculate accurately but to "have a rough skin feeling"
 So it is better to adopt a ratio that is easy to remember without considering the details.

 What is 50 yen per minute?
 	3,000 yen for an hour's work
  8 hours a day, 20 days a month for 12 months, 5,760,000 yen

 You could make it 60 yen per minute and then "[1 yen per second]", only 1.2 times the difference.
